race.comment: ROSIE CAN RUN (8) missed narrowly at Bunbury two back before flying home on the Scarpside last start over 1700m. She drops back to the mile today but draws the inside now. She can sit closer than she did last start, she drops in weight and she looks the one to beat on her recent form. GOLDEN KATHLEEN (1) finished off strongly last start over the 1500m journey last start and should appreciate the slight rise to the mile. She'll likely be back in the run from the barrier, but her recent form stacks right up and she's sure to be flashing late in the race. REBELNADO (5) is looking for the hat-trick today after a narrow win at Albany 47 days ago. He carries less weight today and the form out of his last start has stood up. Can be flying late. CHEYNE BAY (2) was good from midfield first-up over 1400m and will be better for that effort. Ticks a few boxes today and won't be far away. MY HARV (6) is better than she showed last time out and is not to be discounted.
